\f2\b\fs27 \cf0 2.	Universal validation versus search history\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa60\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 Context:
\f1\b0  Two separate issues were getting mixed together. Every surviving strategy should provide the same required evidence, but a winner discovered after millions of adaptive attempts is statistically less surprising than a winner from one untouched hypothesis.\

\f2\b Question:
\f1\b0  Should all survivors face the same mandatory evidence requirements while the anti-selection-bias correction becomes stricter as Montauk searches more broadly and repeatedly?\

\f2\b Suggested answer:
\f1\b0  Yes. Use one common Gold evidence contract, and separately account for the complete search path, including agent feedback cycles and discarded attempts.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Reasoning:
\f1\b0  Author identity should not create an easier certification route. At the same time, ignoring the number of attempts would let continual search manufacture lucky winners.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

