\f2\b\fs27 \cf0 3.	Retire T0/T1/T2 routing\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa60\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 Context:
\f1\b0  The current validator can route strategies through different tiers based partly on how they were proposed. Some tiers may skip tests or redistribute their score weights. That conflicts with your desire for every Gold strategy to survive the strongest available process.\

\f2\b Question:
\f1\b0  Should 3.0 remove author-origin tiers as a reason to skip or weaken evidence requirements?\

\f2\b Suggested answer:
\f1\b0  Yes. Require the same evidence planks and rigor for every survivor. Permit only a predeclared equivalent test or a genuinely valid not-applicable result when a test is structurally irrelevant.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Reasoning:
\f1\b0  This closes an avoidable loophole. Selection history still matters, but it belongs inside multiplicity and overfitting tests rather than in a shortcut around them.\
