\f2\b\fs27 \cf0 4.	Required real-data horizons\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa60\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 Context:
\f1\b0  "Beats B&H in all real data" needs named tests. One result over TECL's entire life can hide a strategy that was excellent early and ineffective recently; many hand-picked subperiods create another data-mining problem.\

\f2\b Question:
\f1\b0  Which fixed real-data horizons must each independently beat B&H before Gold is possible?\

\f2\b Suggested answer:
\f1\b0  Require the complete available real TECL history and one fixed trailing five-year real-data horizon. Treat named crashes and stress episodes as frozen diagnostics unless the validation design establishes a small predeclared set of additional hard gates.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Reasoning:
\f1\b0  Full history tests durability; the fixed recent window tests present usefulness. Avoiding an expanding collection of hand-selected windows reduces the chance of tuning the exam to past events.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

