\f2\b\fs27 \cf0 6.	Synthetic catastrophic veto\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa60\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 Context:
\f1\b0  Synthetic scenarios can expose mechanical fragility outside the one market history we observed, but they are generated assumptions rather than independent evidence. The question is whether an extreme synthetic failure merely lowers confidence or prevents Gold.\

\f2\b Question:
\f1\b0  Should synthetic results ever veto Gold, and if so only for what kind of failure?\

\f2\b Suggested answer:
\f1\b0  Keep synthetic performance diagnostic except for a narrow predeclared catastrophic veto: repeated ruin, invalid behavior, or breach of a frozen maximum-loss safety limit across a broad set of validated stress scenarios. One bad synthetic path does not veto Gold, and synthetic success never counts as independent proof of edge.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Reasoning:
\f1\b0  This catches structural danger without letting arbitrary scenario generation become a second tunable Gold exam. The validator must define and test the exact catastrophe threshold before use.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

