\f2\b\fs27 \cf0 10.	Minimum evidence\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa60\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 Context:
\f1\b0  A strategy can show excellent performance from only a handful of trades or one macro regime. Simplicity reduces parameter-overfit risk but does not create missing observations.\

\f2\b Question:
\f1\b0  What evidence floor must be met before statistical passage can mean Gold?\

\f2\b Suggested answer:
\f1\b0  Require a validated minimum track-record-length/power test plus explicit trade-count and independent-regime reporting. Do not choose an arbitrary trade count as the sole gate. If the record is too thin, return "insufficient evidence" rather than Gold, even for a simple strategy.\
