\f2\fs27 \cf0 16.	Search-campaign identity\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa60\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 Context:
\f1\b0  Multiple-testing corrections need to know which alternatives were considered together. Montauk will search continuously, so an arbitrary midnight, model session, or file boundary must not make prior attempts disappear statistically.\

\f2\b Question:
\f1\b0  How should Montauk identify the nested search history associated with a winner?\

\f2\b Suggested answer:
\f1\b0  Preserve hierarchical IDs for family version, agent batch, research campaign, data vintage, engine/validator contract, and lifetime board history. Let the statistical design use the relevant levels; never let one ID reset the others.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Reasoning:
\f1\b0  There is no single honest boundary for an adaptive lifelong search. Hierarchical provenance allows within-family, campaign-wide, and board/lifetime questions to be tested without pretending earlier exploration never occurred.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

